477  /// copy constructor implementation
478  String::String(const String& obj) {
479  /// object member can be just copied by value
480  this->value = obj.value;
481 
482  /// if there is a token, make copy
483  if (obj.token) {
484  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
485  }
486 
487  /// set parents
488  set_parent_in_children();
489  }

551 
552  /// copy constructor implementation
553  Integer::Integer(const Integer& obj) {
554  /// object member can be just copied by value
555  this->value = obj.value;
556  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
557  if (obj.macro) {
558  this->macro.reset(obj.macro->clone());
559  }
560 
561  /// if there is a token, make copy
562  if (obj.token) {
563  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
564  }
565 
566  /// set parents
567  set_parent_in_children();
568  }
569 
570 
571  /// set this parent in the children
572  void Integer::set_parent_in_children() {
573 
574  /// optional member could be nullptr
575  if (macro) {
576  macro->set_parent(this);
577  }
578 
579  }

2586 /**
2587  * \brief Erase members to definitions
2588  */
2589 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first, AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator last) {
2590  return definitions.erase(first, last);
2591 }
2592 /**
2593  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to definitions
2594  *
2595  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
2596  */
2597 size_t AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(std::unordered_set<AssignedDefinition*>& to_be_erased) {
2598  auto first = definitions.begin();
2599  auto last = definitions.end();
2600  auto result = first;
2601 
2602  while (first != last) {
2603  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
2604  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
2605  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
2606  reset_assigned_definition(result, *first);
2607  ++result;
2608  }
2609  ++first;
2610  }
2611 
2612  size_t out = last - result;
2613  erase_assigned_definition(result, last);
2614 
2615  return out;
2616 }

3104  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
3105  */
3106 size_t StatementBlock::erase_statement(std::unordered_set<Statement*>& to_be_erased) {
3107  auto first = statements.begin();
3108  auto last = statements.end();
3109  auto result = first;
3110 
3111  while (first != last) {
3112  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while

3117  }
3118  ++first;
3119  }
3120 
3121  size_t out = last - result;
3122  erase_statement(result, last);
3123

4173  void ProcedureBlock::visit_children(visitor::Visitor& v) {
4174  /// use -> for pointer member
4175  name->accept(v);
4176  (void)v;

4178  for (auto& item : this->parameters) {
4179  item->accept(v);
4180  }
4181  (void)v;
4182  /// optional member could be nullptr
4183  if (this->unit) {
4184  this->unit->accept(v);
4185  }
4186  (void)v;
4187  /// use -> for pointer member
4188  statement_block->accept(v);
4189  (void)v;
4190  }

4228  /// copy constructor implementation
4229  ProcedureBlock::ProcedureBlock(const ProcedureBlock& obj) {
4230  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4231  if (obj.name) {
4232  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
4233  }
4234  /// copy each element of vector
4235  for (auto& item : obj.parameters) {
4236  this->parameters.emplace_back(item->clone());
4237  }
4238  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4239  if (obj.unit) {
4240  this->unit.reset(obj.unit->clone());
4241  }
4242  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4243  if (obj.statement_block) {
4244  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
4245  }
4246 
4247  /// if there is a token, make copy
4248  if (obj.token) {
4249  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
4250  }
4251 
4252  /// set parents
4253  set_parent_in_children();
4254  }
4255 
4256 
4257  /// set this parent in the children
4258  void ProcedureBlock::set_parent_in_children() {
4259 
4260  /// optional member could be nullptr
4261  if (name) {
4262  name->set_parent(this);
4263  }
4264  /// set parent for each element of the vector
4265  for (auto& item : parameters) {
4266  item->set_parent(this);
4267 
4268  }
4269  /// optional member could be nullptr
4270  if (unit) {
4271  unit->set_parent(this);
4272  }
4273  /// optional member could be nullptr
4274  if (statement_block) {
4275  statement_block->set_parent(this);
4276  }
4277 
4278  }

6504 
6505  void BinaryExpression::visit_children(visitor::Visitor& v) {
6506  /// use -> for pointer member
6507  lhs->accept(v);
6508  (void)v;
6509  /// use . for object member
6510  op.accept(v);
6511  (void)v;
6512  /// use -> for pointer member
6513  rhs->accept(v);
6514  (void)v;

6524  /// use -> for pointer member
6525  rhs->accept(v);

7912 /**
7913  * \brief Erase member to variables
7914  */
7915 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
7916  return variables.erase(first);
7917 }
7918 /**
7919  * \brief Erase members to variables
7920  */
7921 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first, LocalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
7922  return variables.erase(first, last);
7923 }
7924 /**
7925  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
7926  *
7927  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
7928  */
7929 size_t LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(std::unordered_set<LocalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
7930  auto first = variables.begin();
7931  auto last = variables.end();
7932  auto result = first;
7933 
7934  while (first != last) {
7935  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
7936  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
7937  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
7938  reset_local_var(result, *first);
7939  ++result;
7940  }
7941  ++first;
7942  }
7943 
7944  size_t out = last - result;
7945  erase_local_var(result, last);
7946 
7947  return out;
7948 }

7951  * \brief Insert member to variables
7952  */
7953 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::insert_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<LocalVar>& n) {
7954  n->set_parent(this);
7955  return variables.insert(position, n);
7956 }
7957 
7958 /**
7959  * \brief Reset member to variables
7960  */
7961 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, LocalVar* n) {
7962  //set parents
7963  n->set_parent(this);
7964 
7965  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
7966 }
7967 
7968 /**
7969  * \brief Reset member to variables
7970  */
7971 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<LocalVar> n) {
7972  //set parents
7973  n->set_parent(this);
7974 
7975  variables[position - variables.begin()] = n;
7976 }

8345  }

9614  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());

9617  for (auto& item : obj.elseifs) {
9618  this->elseifs.emplace_back(item->clone());

9621  if (obj.elses) {
9622  this->elses.reset(obj.elses->clone());
9623  }

9628  }

9632  }

9955 /**
9956  * \brief Erase member to statements
9957  */
9958 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first) {
9959  return statements.erase(first);
9960 }
9961 /**
9962  * \brief Erase members to statements
9963  */
9964 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first, WatchVector::const_iterator last) {
9965  return statements.erase(first, last);
9966 }
9967 /**
9968  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
9969  *
9970  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
9971  */
9972 size_t WatchStatement::erase_watch(std::unordered_set<Watch*>& to_be_erased) {
9973  auto first = statements.begin();
9974  auto last = statements.end();
9975  auto result = first;
9976 
9977  while (first != last) {
9978  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
9979  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
9980  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
9981  reset_watch(result, *first);
9982  ++result;
9983  }
9984  ++first;
9985  }
9986 
9987  size_t out = last - result;
9988  erase_watch(result, last);
9989 
9990  return out;
9991 }
9992

9994  * \brief Insert member to statements
9995  */
9996 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::insert_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<Watch>& n) {
9997  n->set_parent(this);
9998  return statements.insert(position, n);
9999 }

10002  * \brief Reset member to statements
10003  */
10004 void WatchStatement::reset_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, Watch* n) {
10005  //set parents
10006  n->set_parent(this);
10007 
10008  statements[position - statements.begin()].reset(n);
10009 }

10675  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy

10678  }

10680  if (obj.expression1) {

10682  }

10685  this->expression2.reset(obj.expression2->clone());

10690  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
10691  }
10692

11875 /**
11876  * \brief Erase member to variables
11877  */
11878 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
11879  return variables.erase(first);
11880 }
11881 /**
11882  * \brief Erase members to variables
11883  */
11884 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first, GlobalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
11885  return variables.erase(first, last);
11886 }
11887 /**
11888  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
11889  *
11890  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
11891  */
11892 size_t Global::erase_global_var(std::unordered_set<GlobalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
11893  auto first = variables.begin();
11894  auto last = variables.end();
11895  auto result = first;
11896 
11897  while (first != last) {
11898  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
11899  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
11900  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
11901  reset_global_var(result, *first);
11902  ++result;
11903  }
11904  ++first;
11905  }
11906 
11907  size_t out = last - result;
11908  erase_global_var(result, last);
11909 
11910  return out;
11911 }

11917  n->set_parent(this);
11918  return variables.insert(position, n);
11919 }

11923  */
11924 void Global::reset_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position, GlobalVar* n) {
11925  //set parents
11926  n->set_parent(this);
11927 
11928  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
11929 }

12137 }
12138 /**
12139  * \brief Erase members to variables
12140  */
12141 PointerVarVector::const_iterator Pointer::erase_pointer_var(PointerVarVector::const_iterator first, PointerVarVector::const_iterator last) {
12142  return variables.erase(first, last);
12143 }
12144 /**
12145  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
12146  *
12147  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
12148  */
12149 size_t Pointer::erase_pointer_var(std::unordered_set<PointerVar*>& to_be_erased) {
12150  auto first = variables.begin();
12151  auto last = variables.end();
12152  auto result = first;
12153 
12154  while (first != last) {
12155  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
12156  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
12157  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
12158  reset_pointer_var(result, *first);
12159  ++result;
12160  }
12161  ++first;
12162  }
12163 
12164  size_t out = last - result;
12165  erase_pointer_var(result, last);
12166 
12167  return out;
12168 }

12174  n->set_parent(this);
12175  return variables.insert(position, n);
12176 }

12839 /**
12840  * \brief Erase members to blocks
12841  */
12842 NodeVector::const_iterator Program::erase_node(NodeVector::const_iterator first, NodeVector::const_iterator last) {
12843  return blocks.erase(first, last);
12844 }
12845 /**
12846  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to blocks
12847  *
12848  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
12849  */
12850 size_t Program::erase_node(std::unordered_set<Node*>& to_be_erased) {
12851  auto first = blocks.begin();
12852  auto last = blocks.end();
12853  auto result = first;
12854 
12855  while (first != last) {
12856  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
12857  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
12858  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
12859  reset_node(result, *first);
12860  ++result;
12861  }
12862  ++first;
12863  }
12864 
12865  size_t out = last - result;
12866  erase_node(result, last);
12867 
12868  return out;
12869 }

12876  return blocks.insert(position, n);
